    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-11-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="331"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51/859</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Secretary of the Treasury</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mellon</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-11-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1927</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to this Department’s letter of
                    November 18,<note n="21" xml:id="d331fn21">Not printed.</note> which transmitted
                    a copy of the formal request of the Austrian Government to the United States
                        Government<note n="22" xml:id="d331fn22">See note from the Austrian
                        Chancellor to the American Minister in Austria, <ref target="#pg_448">p.
                            448</ref>.</note> to grant postponement up to December 31, 1957, of the
                    Austrian bond held by the United States Treasury, I have the honor to transmit
                    for your information a copy of despatch No. 1585, dated October 29, 1927, from
                    the American Minister at Vienna,<note n="22a" xml:id="d331fn22a">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> with its enclosures, regarding the contemplated new Austrian loan.</p>
                <pb facs="0542" n="456" xml:id="pg_456"/>
                <p>You will note the Minister’s statement that he is taking it for granted that the
                    Department will at the proper time take appropriate action to obtain a new
                    Congressional Enabling Act. The Department’s only communication to the Minister
                    on the matter has been that quoted in the Department’s letter to you of November
                    18 to the effect that a new Enabling Act of Congress would be necessary.</p>
                <p>I should be pleased to receive any comment you may care to make on this
                    matter.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. R. Castle</hi>, Jr.</signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
